## Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js project following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart

### Changes Made

**Modified Files:**
- `app/layout.tsx` - Added Analytics component integration
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with new dependency

### Implementation Details

1. **Package Installation:**
   - Installed `@vercel/analytics` package using npm
   - Package version added to dependencies in package.json
   - Lock file updated to ensure consistent dependency resolution

2. **Analytics Configuration:**
   - Imported Analytics component from `@vercel/analytics/next` in the root layout
   - Added `<Analytics />` component inside the body element of the RootLayout
   - Follows Next.js App Router best practices as specified in official docs

3. **Code Changes:**
   - Added import: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";`
   - Placed Analytics component at the end of the body element to track page views
   - Preserved existing code structure and formatting

### Testing & Verification

✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
✅ ESLint passed with no issues
✅ TypeScript compilation successful
✅ No breaking changes to existing functionality

### Next Steps (User Action Required)

To complete the Web Analytics setup:
1. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (navigate to Analytics → click Enable)
2. Deploy the application to Vercel using `vercel deploy`
3. After deployment, analytics data will be visible in the dashboard within a few days

The Analytics component will automatically track page views and is ready to use once deployed to Vercel.
